{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/candana-sutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Standing to one side, the god Candana addressed the Buddha in verse:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“Who here crosses the flood, <br>\ntireless all day and night? <br>\nWho, not standing and unsupported, <br>\ndoes not sink in the deep?” <br>\n<br>\n“Someone who is always endowed with ethics, <br>\nwise and serene, <br>\nenergetic and resolute, <br>\ncrosses the flood so hard to cross. <br>\n<br>\nSomeone who desists from sensual perception, <br>\nhas moved past the fetter of form, <br>\nand has finished with relishing and greed <br>\ndoes not sink in the deep.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN2/vasudatta-sutta/\">SN.2.16. Vāsudatta Sutta (“With Vāsudatta”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Standing to one side, the god Candana addressed the Buddha in verse:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“Who here crosses the flood, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\ntireless all day and night? "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nWho, not standing and unsupported, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\ndoes not sink in the deep?” "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n“Someone who is always endowed with ethics, "},{"type":"element","tagName"